{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XiRZ79WmcAciE6msWuHCFL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me provide you with the complete information you requested:\n\n## settle-tx.ts — Full Analysis\n\n### SettleTxDeps Interface (Lines 58-64)\n```typescript\nexport interface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n}\n```\n\n### How Settlement Currently Works\n\n**settleMatch (Lines 213-415)** — Coinflip settlement:\n1. Retrieves secret from DB via `db.getRoundByPda(pda)`\n2. Transitions phase from `locked` → `settling`\n3. Logs operator event: `settle_submitted`\n4. Fetches in parallel: match account, platform config, entropy, blockhash\n5. Decodes match account (creator, opponent, creatorSide, entryAmount, algoVer)\n6. Pre-computes result via `deriveResult(secret, entropy, matchPdaBytes, algoVer)`\n7. Calculates fee and payout\n8. Builds settle instruction (8 accounts) and submits transaction\n9. Confirms transaction\n10. **Updates DB** (lines 348-368):\n    - `db.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"settled\", { settle_tx, result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_attempts })`\n    - `db.updateRoundEntries(pda, coinflipEntries)` — persists entries in JSONB column\n    - `db.insertOperatorEvent(pda, \"settle_confirmed\", {...})`\n    - `db.insertTransaction({...})` — payout tx record\n11. **Calls referral hook** (lines 381-390): `recordReferralEarnings(db, {...})`\n\n**settleLordRound (Lines 417-626)** — Lord of RNGs settlement:\n- Similar flow but handles weighted entries and calculates winning entry via modulo\n- Persists entries via `db.updateRoundEntries(pda, serializedEntries)`\n- Also calls `recordReferralEarnings(db, {...)` with all players\n\n### How DB Writes Are Structured\n\n**NOT in an explicit transaction** — each DB write is a separate call:\n- `db.updateRoundPhase()` — single write\n- `db.updateRoundEntries()` — separate write\n- `db.insertOperatorEvent()` — separate write\n- `db.insertTransaction()` — separate write\n- `recordReferralEarnings()` internally calls `db.getReferralLinkByReferee()`, `db.getReferrerRate()`, `db.insertReferralEarning()` — separate writes\n\n**Critical note**: If settlement crashes between `updateRoundPhase` and later writes, the round is marked settled but referral earnings are incomplete. The `recordReferralEarnings()` function handles this via idempotency (UNIQUE constraint catches retries).\n\n### recordReferralEarnings Hook (Lines 113-195)\n\nCalled in both `settleMatch` and `settleLordRound` **after all settlement writes**. It:\n1. Deduplicates players (Lord can have multiple entries per wallet)\n2. For each unique player wallet:\n   - Looks up referral link via `db.getReferralLinkByReferee(wallet)`\n   - If referrer exists, fetches referrer's rate via `db.getReferrerRate(referrerWallet, referralDefaultRateBps)`\n   - Calculates: `feeLamports = (wagerLamports * feeBps) / 10_000`\n   - Calculates: `referrerEarned = (feeLamports * referrerRateBps) / 10_000`\n   - Calculates: `refereeRebate = (feeLamports * 1000) / 10_000` (fixed 10%)\n   - Calls `db.insertReferralEarning({...})`\n3. Catches errors silently (logs but doesn't throw) — referral failure must not fail settlement\n4. Handles idempotency via UNIQUE constraint on duplicate key errors\n\n### How sql (Postgres Connection) Is Used\n\nFrom index.ts (lines 31-33):\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);\nconst authDb = createAuthDb(sql);\n```\n\nThe `sql` object (native postgres client) is:\n- Passed to `createAuthDb(sql)` for auth operations\n- Passed to referral routes via `createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config })`\n- Passed to Close Call clock worker via `createCloseCallClockWorker({ ..., db: sql })`\n- Passed to event queue worker via `createEventWorker(sql, {...})`\n- Passed to health routes via `createHealthRoutes({ ..., sql, ... })`\n\nThe `db` object (wrapper around postgres) is used for game settlement, round queries, and referral lookups in settle-tx.ts.\n\n### How settle-tx is Initialized (index.ts lines 117-126)\n\n```typescript\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) =>\n    settleRound(\n      { db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, entropyAccount, referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps },\n      pda,\n    ),\n});\n```\n\nThe `SettleTxDeps` is constructed inline with:\n- `db` — Db instance\n- `connection` — RPC Connection\n- `serverKeypair` — from `config.serverKeypair`\n- `entropyAccount` — from `config.entropyAccount` (converted to PublicKey at line 117)\n- `referralDefaultRateBps` — from `config.referralDefaultRateBps`\n\n## Summary\n\n**Settlement is NOT wrapped in DB transactions.** It's a sequence of separate writes:\n1. Phase update → settled\n2. Entries persist\n3. Operator event log\n4. Payout transaction record\n5. **Referral earnings** (idempotent, errors absorbed)\n\nThe referral hook is called **after on-chain settlement confirms** and is designed to be resilient to failures via UNIQUE constraint idempotency."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac428c8ea998a2221 (use SendMessage with to: 'ac428c8ea998a2221' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53258\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 44839</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b75d7aec-4dd6-4c16-a100-27ad57796fa9","uuid":"754eec1f-3b34-474f-8ce5-a53c4d7629f8","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:27:30.565Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full contents of the file `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/settle-tx.ts`. I need to understand:\n1. How settlement currently works (settleMatch, settleLordRound)\n2. How DB writes are structured (are they already in a transaction?)\n3. Where `recordReferralEarnings` is called\n4. What the `SettleTxDeps` interface looks like\n5. How `sql` (postgres connection) is used\n\nAlso read `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts` to see how settle-tx is initialized and what deps are passed.\n\nReturn the FULL file contents of settle-tx.ts and the relevant section of index.ts where settle-tx deps are created.","agentId":"ac428c8ea998a2221","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me provide you with the complete information you requested:\n\n## settle-tx.ts — Full Analysis\n\n### SettleTxDeps Interface (Lines 58-64)\n```typescript\nexport interface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n}\n```\n\n### How Settlement Currently Works\n\n**settleMatch (Lines 213-415)** — Coinflip settlement:\n1. Retrieves secret from DB via `db.getRoundByPda(pda)`\n2. Transitions phase from `locked` → `settling`\n3. Logs operator event: `settle_submitted`\n4. Fetches in parallel: match account, platform config, entropy, blockhash\n5. Decodes match account (creator, opponent, creatorSide, entryAmount, algoVer)\n6. Pre-computes result via `deriveResult(secret, entropy, matchPdaBytes, algoVer)`\n7. Calculates fee and payout\n8. Builds settle instruction (8 accounts) and submits transaction\n9. Confirms transaction\n10. **Updates DB** (lines 348-368):\n    - `db.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"settled\", { settle_tx, result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_attempts })`\n    - `db.updateRoundEntries(pda, coinflipEntries)` — persists entries in JSONB column\n    - `db.insertOperatorEvent(pda, \"settle_confirmed\", {...})`\n    - `db.insertTransaction({...})` — payout tx record\n11. **Calls referral hook** (lines 381-390): `recordReferralEarnings(db, {...})`\n\n**settleLordRound (Lines 417-626)** — Lord of RNGs settlement:\n- Similar flow but handles weighted entries and calculates winning entry via modulo\n- Persists entries via `db.updateRoundEntries(pda, serializedEntries)`\n- Also calls `recordReferralEarnings(db, {...)` with all players\n\n### How DB Writes Are Structured\n\n**NOT in an explicit transaction** — each DB write is a separate call:\n- `db.updateRoundPhase()` — single write\n- `db.updateRoundEntries()` — separate write\n- `db.insertOperatorEvent()` — separate write\n- `db.insertTransaction()` — separate write\n- `recordReferralEarnings()` internally calls `db.getReferralLinkByReferee()`, `db.getReferrerRate()`, `db.insertReferralEarning()` — separate writes\n\n**Critical note**: If settlement crashes between `updateRoundPhase` and later writes, the round is marked settled but referral earnings are incomplete. The `recordReferralEarnings()` function handles this via idempotency (UNIQUE constraint catches retries).\n\n### recordReferralEarnings Hook (Lines 113-195)\n\nCalled in both `settleMatch` and `settleLordRound` **after all settlement writes**. It:\n1. Deduplicates players (Lord can have multiple entries per wallet)\n2. For each unique player wallet:\n   - Looks up referral link via `db.getReferralLinkByReferee(wallet)`\n   - If referrer exists, fetches referrer's rate via `db.getReferrerRate(referrerWallet, referralDefaultRateBps)`\n   - Calculates: `feeLamports = (wagerLamports * feeBps) / 10_000`\n   - Calculates: `referrerEarned = (feeLamports * referrerRateBps) / 10_000`\n   - Calculates: `refereeRebate = (feeLamports * 1000) / 10_000` (fixed 10%)\n   - Calls `db.insertReferralEarning({...})`\n3. Catches errors silently (logs but doesn't throw) — referral failure must not fail settlement\n4. Handles idempotency via UNIQUE constraint on duplicate key errors\n\n### How sql (Postgres Connection) Is Used\n\nFrom index.ts (lines 31-33):\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);\nconst authDb = createAuthDb(sql);\n```\n\nThe `sql` object (native postgres client) is:\n- Passed to `createAuthDb(sql)` for auth operations\n- Passed to referral routes via `createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config })`\n- Passed to Close Call clock worker via `createCloseCallClockWorker({ ..., db: sql })`\n- Passed to event queue worker via `createEventWorker(sql, {...})`\n- Passed to health routes via `createHealthRoutes({ ..., sql, ... })`\n\nThe `db` object (wrapper around postgres) is used for game settlement, round queries, and referral lookups in settle-tx.ts.\n\n### How settle-tx is Initialized (index.ts lines 117-126)\n\n```typescript\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) =>\n    settleRound(\n      { db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, entropyAccount, referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps },\n      pda,\n    ),\n});\n```\n\nThe `SettleTxDeps` is constructed inline with:\n- `db` — Db instance\n- `connection` — RPC Connection\n- `serverKeypair` — from `config.serverKeypair`\n- `entropyAccount` — from `config.entropyAccount` (converted to PublicKey at line 117)\n- `referralDefaultRateBps` — from `config.referralDefaultRateBps`\n\n## Summary\n\n**Settlement is NOT wrapped in DB transactions.** It's a sequence of separate writes:\n1. Phase update → settled\n2. Entries persist\n3. Operator event log\n4. Payout transaction record\n5. **Referral earnings** (idempotent, errors absorbed)\n\nThe referral hook is called **after on-chain settlement confirms** and is designed to be resilient to failures via UNIQUE constraint idempotency."}],"totalDurationMs":44839,"totalTokens":53258,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":3065,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14387,"cache_read_input_tokens":34261,"output_tokens":1545,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14387},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
